s hosts who have thrown resources into the cause as hosts.\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1504, \"end\": 1510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998563280418, \"rank\": 1.2848769834366993e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9976141293975233, \"rank\": 0.002114817287692243, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without putting a number on it, Team SA will be looking to better their tally ofthreemedals from Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1668, \"end\": 1670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.48438222075062e-23, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1728, \"end\": 1733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9976141293975233, \"rank\": 0.002114817287692243, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And they should achieve that, although we are not comparing apples with apples when it comes to \\\"us\\\" and \\\"them\\\".\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's not to say that there are not giants among the Team SA athletes who are represented in 19 different codes.\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1913, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.48438222075062e-23, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am thinking that there are a handful of names who would not be out of place in Team USA colours.\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2049, \"end\": 2057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8356509307233977, \"rank\": 0.19586610223234116, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They include track athletes Akani Simbine and Wayde van Niekerk, swimmers Tatjana Smith and Pieter Coetze (and despite his age, perhaps Chad Le Clos),\\u00a0surfer Jordy Smith, and even our golfers.\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2095, \"end\": 2108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}, {\"begin\": 2113, \"end\": 2130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wayde van Niekerk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\"}, {\"begin\": 2203, \"end\": 2215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chad Le Clos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\"}, {\"begin\": 2225, \"end\": 2236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordy_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordy Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordy_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordy_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Plus, the men's Sevens rugby players will fancy their chances if they come up against Team USA.\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2277, \"end\": 2289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sevens rugby\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\"}, {\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8356509307233977, \"rank\": 0.19586610223234116, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the sheer weight of resources counts more than isolated talent.\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The visual of Team USA's building within the village brings home the enormity of the task though.\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2445, \"end\": 2453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8356509307233977, \"rank\": 0.19586610223234116, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are being represented by some 600 athletes coming from a country that has a 330-million population.\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2633, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Much of their squad is fully professional, whereas much of Team SA's members have day (and night) jobs and have to fit in their sports careers either side of work.\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2698, \"end\": 2700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.48438222075062e-23, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Which is why every medal Team SA wins is celebrated with gusto.\", \"from\": 2799, \"to\": 2862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2829, \"end\": 2831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.48438222075062e-23, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a while the USA will be counting their golds more than they will silver or bronze.\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2881, \"end\": 2884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997209277950446, \"rank\": 0.00027907078207280563, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After all, their 39 golds were down on the 46 and 48 of the two previous Games'.\", \"from\": 2952, \"to\": 3032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only twice in the last 10 Olympics' stretching back to 1984 in Los Angeles have the USA not hit 100 medals, with their lowest being 93 at Sydney 2000.\", \"from\": 3033, \"to\": 3183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3096, \"end\": 3107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999737228794, \"rank\": 2.5525600241784878e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 3117, \"end\": 3120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997209277950446, \"rank\": 0.00027907078207280563, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Therefore, a betting person would probably lay the line at 40 gold medals for them in Paris.\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3271, \"end\": 3276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.579254491612435e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, when judging one's own country, one needs to get the full picture in terms of size and resources.\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3379, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the context is: should Team USA not reach 110 medals, or 40 golds, then they will feel that they have under-achieved.\", \"from\": 3380, \"to\": 3501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3407, \"end\": 3415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8356509307233977, \"rank\": 0.19586610223234116, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gary Lemke is reporting live from Paris for the Team SA website for the duration of the Paris Olympics 2024  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring!\", \"from\": 3503